BOLA BAMIGBOLA Osun State Governor, Adegboyega Oyetola, on Saturday promised to support the proposed Federal College of Education in Iwo and ensure its smooth take-off. Oyetola also commended the President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd), for the consideration given to the state as a beneficiary of the proposed institution. Receiving members of the Technical Team of the Federal Ministry of Education and the National Commission for Colleges of Education at the Government House, Osogbo, Oyetola said the establishment of more colleges of education in the country would further contribute significantly to the development of vocational and technical education in Nigeria. Oyetola said, “Our state is particularly ready for this gesture. We see the institution as a very big gift. We have all it takes to ensure the take-off of academic activities.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 